		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">TmEE wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">This method was used in a lot of earlier arcade machines.</div><br />It was also used in this <a href="http://youtu.be/zk-QhYE4jxw" class="postlink">Atari 2600 Raycaster</a>, because rays are cast horizontally while the screen is drawn vertically. It still looks pretty bad though... Personally I'd have tried using some interpolation and player/missile graphics to smooth out the edges of the walls.<br /><br />EDIT: Also, I seriously considered using this &quot;mod&quot; with the MSX, in order to make a side-scroller with pixel-perfect scrolling. Sprite limitations are pretty severe on the TMS9918, so there would be some benefit in this area too. I think I consider a vertical sprite limitation less annoying than a horizontal one.

		

		</td>
